<h1 id="set-up-lease-approval-workflows">Set up lease approval workflows</h1>


<p>The topic explains how to set up an approval workflow that will run when a new lease is created. For information about how to use the workflow, see <a href="use-create-lease-wrkflw.html">Use lease approval workflows</a>.</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Go to <strong>Asset leasing &gt; Setup &gt; Lease workflow</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Lease workflow</strong> page, select <strong>New</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the dialog box that appears, under <strong>Workflow type</strong>, select the <strong>Lease workflow</strong> link.</p>
<p>The application is opened. After it runs, sign in to Azure Active Directory (Azure AD) to be redirected to the workflow application.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Drag the <strong>Lease workflow approval</strong> element onto the workflow.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Connect one node from <strong>Start</strong> to <strong>Lease workflow approval</strong>. Then connect <strong>Lease workflow approval</strong> to <strong>End</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Double-click <strong>Lease workflow approval</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Properties</strong>, and then, under <strong>Basic settings</strong>, enter a name for the workflow.</p>
<p>On this page, you can also set more parameters for the workflow. If you've turned on <strong>Automatic actions</strong>, the system will automatically take a specific action. Notifications can be sent if they are specified on the <strong>Notifications</strong> tab. On the <strong>Advanced settings</strong> tab, you can specify a final approver, set a time limit, and designate specific actions that must be completed.</p>
</li>
<li><p>When you've finished setting the workflow parameters, select <strong>Close</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Step 1</strong>, and then select <strong>Properties</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Under <strong>Basic settings</strong>, enter a name for the step, create a subject line for the approval, and specify instructions for the approval.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Assignment</strong> page, select the assignment type.</p>
</li>
<li><p>To assign specific users to the approval, select <strong>User</strong>, select the users who approve leases, and then select <strong>Close</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Save and close</strong> to create the workflow. Then, when you're prompted, select <strong>OK</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Create workflow</strong> page, select <strong>Close</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select the new workflow, and then select <strong>Versions</strong>. Then select <strong>Make active</strong> to ensure that the workflow is active.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Close</strong>. The new active version appears.</p>
</li>
</ol>
